          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Palo Alto, CA</p>
  <h1>Java Software Engineer - Revenue Infrastructure</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>THE TEAM
The Revenue Infrastructure Team is a small team at the heart of Ning. Simply put, we build and maintain the systems responsible for collecting the money. Our systems need to not only scale with the Ning but also provide the robustness, reliability and security required of a billing system. As Ning innovates with new payment methods, revenue sharing, partnership and affiliate programs, we need to rapidly develop and adapt new features to meet the changing needs. We are looking for innovative, motivated engineers who will take ownership and help drive the product at all levels.</p>

<p>THE OPPORTUNITY
* Work end-to-end on development within a small agile team, deploy your own changes and  interact directly product management
* Design, Develop and deploy robust, scalable product features to support subscription management, payment collection and revenue sharing.
* Drive design discussions with architects, operations and other engineering teams</p>

<p>THE QUALIFICATIONS
* Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Engineering, Computer Science, or related technical field.
* At least 7 years software engineering experience.
Including:</p>

<ul>
<li>Designing and developing modern web-based server solutions</li>
<li>Agile Process or Rapid development cycles</li>
<li>Experience in large-scale systems or transactional, financial or billing related systems</li>
<li>Expert in Java development and debugging, SQL, Internet protocols and technologies including HTTP, SSL, DNS, TCP/IP, XML, JSON, and RSS. Experience with Ruby, Javascript, PHP and CSS a plus.</li>
<li>Solid understanding and practical experience in Object Oriented Design &amp; Programming, Design Patterns, Software Development life cycle process and procedures.</li>
</ul>

</div><!-- /.column.main -->

